EU to Boost Bank Capital Ratio Requirement, Economista Says

-- B y   C h a r l e s   P e n t y
-- 
2011-10-21T06:15:21Z

-- http://www.bloomberg.com/news/2011-10-21/eu-to-boost-bank-capital-ratio-requirement-economista-says.html
The European Union would set a
higher capital ratio for banks in return for not imposing so-
called haircuts on sovereign-debt holdings,  El Economista 
reported, citing people familiar with the negotiations.  The EU plans to require a ratio for maximum quality bank
capital of 10 percent rather than the 9 percent discussed up to
now, the newspaper said.  To contact the reporter on this story:
Charles Penty in Madrid at 
 cpenty@bloomberg.net   To contact the editor responsible for this story:
Frank Connelly at 
 fconnelly@bloomberg.net  